1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,880
 And we thank you for this in Jesus' name.

2
00:00:02,880 --> 00:00:05,280
 Everyone says, Amen.

3
00:00:05,280 --> 00:00:07,440
 Amen. Amen.

4
00:00:07,440 --> 00:00:08,160
 Have a seat.

5
00:00:08,160 --> 00:00:12,240
 You know, one of the things that's so important for us to understand

6
00:00:12,240 --> 00:00:14,560
 is that for over 2000 years,

7
00:00:14,560 --> 00:00:19,280
 God has shaped his church through the use of his prophetic voice.

8
00:00:19,280 --> 00:00:24,400
 One of the most profound things that we have as Christians

9
00:00:24,400 --> 00:00:27,840
 is this idea that we worship a speaking God.

10
00:00:27,840 --> 00:00:28,240
 Amen.

11
00:00:29,600 --> 00:00:30,320
 I'm gonna try that again.

12
00:00:30,320 --> 00:00:31,440
 We worship a speaking God.

13
00:00:31,440 --> 00:00:31,760
 Amen.

14
00:00:31,760 --> 00:00:37,360
 And when we worship a speaking God, what that means is that our God is not distant and removed,

15
00:00:37,360 --> 00:00:41,360
 but our God is present and active in the world at this time.

16
00:00:41,360 --> 00:00:48,240
 And it's a profound thing that God shapes his church over years and years and years

17
00:00:48,240 --> 00:00:50,560
 by the use of his prophetic voice.

18
00:00:50,560 --> 00:00:55,040
 In fact, the apostle John, as he's writing at the end of the New Testament

19
00:00:55,040 --> 00:00:56,320
 about the end of all things,

20
00:00:56,880 --> 00:01:02,080
 as on the Isle of Patmos, he gets this vision of what the world would be like at the end of all things.

21
00:01:02,080 --> 00:01:05,520
 The start of that vision begins with words to the churches.

22
00:01:05,520 --> 00:01:11,520
 And so he sees the churches in Asia Minor, which were the churches in his time.

23
00:01:11,520 --> 00:01:17,920
 And he sees a picture of Jesus standing over those churches, and Jesus speaks some words.

24
00:01:17,920 --> 00:01:19,760
 And these words are really important.

25
00:01:19,760 --> 00:01:22,320
 Jesus stands over the church and he says this.

26
00:01:22,320 --> 00:01:29,120
 He says, "Let those who have ears, let them hear what the Spirit is saying to the churches."

27
00:01:29,120 --> 00:01:30,640
 Say that again.

28
00:01:30,640 --> 00:01:36,160
 "Those that have ears, let them hear what the Spirit is saying to the churches."

29
00:01:36,160 --> 00:01:40,240
 And for 2000 years, the Spirit has been speaking to the church.

30
00:01:40,240 --> 00:01:46,800
 Our Anglican friends use that prayer a lot in their services, in the liturgy of their services,

31
00:01:46,800 --> 00:01:49,920
 that they might hear what the Spirit is saying to the church.

32
00:01:49,920 --> 00:01:55,200
 This is what has driven Vision Sunday here at the Vine over the last 15 years

33
00:01:55,200 --> 00:01:56,480
 that we've been doing Vision Sunday.

34
00:01:56,480 --> 00:01:59,520
 That we have a God who is speaking to us.

35
00:01:59,520 --> 00:02:02,960
 And I think now more than ever in history,

36
00:02:02,960 --> 00:02:06,160
 even off the back of all the things that we saw happen last night in the Middle East,

37
00:02:06,160 --> 00:02:09,920
 with everything that's taken place in the uprising of this world,

38
00:02:09,920 --> 00:02:14,240
 in the shaking that seems to be happening in the foundations across this world,

39
00:02:14,240 --> 00:02:17,600
 our God is still alive and he is still speaking.

40
00:02:18,640 --> 00:02:21,040
 And the beauty is, is that we as his people,

41
00:02:21,040 --> 00:02:24,480
 we have a role to play in the environment of a speaking God.

42
00:02:24,480 --> 00:02:28,000
 And our role is to recognize that he is speaking.

43
00:02:28,000 --> 00:02:32,160
 It's to quieten ourselves enough that we can hear his voice,

44
00:02:32,160 --> 00:02:37,840
 understand it, then internalize it, proclaim it, and live it.

45
00:02:37,840 --> 00:02:43,120
 We do not have a God speaking problem in the world today.

46
00:02:43,120 --> 00:02:43,620
 Amen?

47
00:02:44,240 --> 00:02:50,320
 But I do think at times we have a listening and acting on that word problem in the church today.

48
00:02:50,320 --> 00:02:52,400
 Can I say that again one more time?

49
00:02:52,400 --> 00:02:55,600
 I don't think we have a problem in the world today with God speaking.

50
00:02:55,600 --> 00:03:01,520
 I think the challenge is, is the church listening and responding?

51
00:03:01,520 --> 00:03:06,880
 And one of the beautiful things is, is that when God's word comes,

52
00:03:06,880 --> 00:03:12,080
 it is the only thing in this world that brings people fully alive.

53
00:03:12,960 --> 00:03:16,000
 This is one of the things that has been woven into the fabric of our creation

54
00:03:16,000 --> 00:03:18,320
 as human beings made in the image of God.

55
00:03:18,320 --> 00:03:20,960
 That if we want to come fully alive,

56
00:03:20,960 --> 00:03:24,240
 if we want to really be the people that God has called us to be,

57
00:03:24,240 --> 00:03:28,720
 the only way that happens is that we become people of the word of God.

58
00:03:28,720 --> 00:03:35,520
 That when God's living word speaks, we receive, we respond, and we act.

59
00:03:35,520 --> 00:03:38,160
 That's what makes us the people of God.

60
00:03:38,160 --> 00:03:42,480
 There's this moment in the New Testament at the end of the gospel of Luke,

61
00:03:42,480 --> 00:03:45,680
 where Jesus appears in his resurrection to two disciples

62
00:03:45,680 --> 00:03:47,600
 who are walking on the road to Emmaus.

63
00:03:47,600 --> 00:03:49,280
 And Jesus has just died on the cross.

64
00:03:49,280 --> 00:03:53,120
 And these two disciples are wrestling with all that's happening in the world.

65
00:03:53,120 --> 00:03:54,960
 And they had thought Jesus was the Messiah,

66
00:03:54,960 --> 00:03:56,960
 but then they'd just seen him die on the cross.

67
00:03:56,960 --> 00:04:00,960
 And so they're thinking, "Okay, well, I guess he wasn't what he claimed to be.

68
00:04:00,960 --> 00:04:02,560
 I guess he's just a prophet."

69
00:04:02,560 --> 00:04:05,680
 And Jesus comes alongside of them, and Jesus does this amazing thing.

70
00:04:05,680 --> 00:04:09,440
 And if you could ever transform into one moment in history, this is the moment.

71
00:04:09,440 --> 00:04:14,480
 Jesus opens up the Old Testament narrative to help them to understand

72
00:04:14,480 --> 00:04:19,680
 how he is the culmination of everything that was spoken about him in the Old Testament.

73
00:04:19,680 --> 00:04:21,680
 Could you imagine what?

74
00:04:21,680 --> 00:04:24,080
 That is the greatest sermon that was ever preached.

75
00:04:24,080 --> 00:04:28,160
 Jesus saying, "Let me tell you the story of Israel,

76
00:04:28,160 --> 00:04:31,360
 and how I am the centerpiece of that story.

77
00:04:31,360 --> 00:04:35,840
 And my death and resurrection now begins a new journey of that story."

78
00:04:35,840 --> 00:04:40,800
 And later, as those two disciples are sitting, having a meal with Jesus,

79
00:04:40,800 --> 00:04:43,280
 Jesus takes bread, he breaks it, he offers it to them.

80
00:04:43,280 --> 00:04:47,200
 They realize, their eyes are open, they realize who he is, and he disappears from them.

81
00:04:47,200 --> 00:04:48,800
 I don't know how that happened, but it happened.

82
00:04:48,800 --> 00:04:53,680
 And as Jesus disappears, they turn to each other, and here's what they say.

83
00:04:53,680 --> 00:05:00,480
 They say, "Were not our hearts burning within us when he spoke the word over us?"

84
00:05:00,480 --> 00:05:03,520
 In other words, they were like,

85
00:05:03,520 --> 00:05:06,080
 "Have we ever been more fully alive than right now?"

86
00:05:06,080 --> 00:05:10,800
 Like we've just had the Messiah speak to us, and we've received it,

87
00:05:10,800 --> 00:05:13,360
 and it's turned and changed us and transformed us.

88
00:05:13,360 --> 00:05:16,160
 And he is alive, and he is who he says he was.

89
00:05:16,160 --> 00:05:19,520
 The word of God always brings his people alive.

90
00:05:19,520 --> 00:05:23,360
 And so Vision Sunday, the reason why I get so excited about Vision Sunday,

91
00:05:23,360 --> 00:05:28,240
 is because we take one Sunday a year to unpack as a leadership here in the church,

92
00:05:28,240 --> 00:05:31,520
 what we think the word of God is saying to us.

93
00:05:32,240 --> 00:05:37,440
 And the reason why we do it is 'cause our desperate cry and prayer

94
00:05:37,440 --> 00:05:39,920
 is that you would become fully alive.

95
00:05:39,920 --> 00:05:43,600
 The very people that God has called you to be.

96
00:05:43,600 --> 00:05:48,160
 Like, could you imagine how Hong Kong would be transformed

97
00:05:48,160 --> 00:05:53,040
 if in the churches of the city, people were truly fully alive?

98
00:05:53,040 --> 00:05:58,080
 Truly the people that God had called them and created them to be.

99
00:05:58,080 --> 00:06:01,680
 So as I start Vision Sunday here in 2026,

100
00:06:01,680 --> 00:06:02,720
 here's my prayer for us.

101
00:06:02,720 --> 00:06:06,400
 That as we peel back a little bit and take a look at some of the things

102
00:06:06,400 --> 00:06:07,680
 that God is saying to us,

103
00:06:07,680 --> 00:06:12,400
 that something inside of you will be like those two disciples on the road to Emmaus.

104
00:06:12,400 --> 00:06:15,760
 That something would burn within you.

105
00:06:15,760 --> 00:06:19,680
 And I'm gonna talk about a lot of things here, just warning you up front.

106
00:06:19,680 --> 00:06:21,200
 There's a lot of information coming.

107
00:06:21,200 --> 00:06:24,640
 But it's not just information, it is revelation.

108
00:06:24,640 --> 00:06:27,680
 And I want you, as I go through this,

109
00:06:27,680 --> 00:06:30,560
 to be prayerful in receiving what I'm saying.

110
00:06:30,560 --> 00:06:31,280
 Does that make sense?

111
00:06:31,760 --> 00:06:34,240
 I'm hoping you do that every Sunday in sermons,

112
00:06:34,240 --> 00:06:35,840
 but I'm not just gonna assume that.

113
00:06:35,840 --> 00:06:38,800
 So I wanna encourage you to be prayerful as I speak,

114
00:06:38,800 --> 00:06:41,680
 because I believe that there is something I'm going to say

115
00:06:41,680 --> 00:06:45,200
 where you will feel your heart burning within you.

116
00:06:45,200 --> 00:06:49,760
 And as that happens, that's for you to go,

117
00:06:49,760 --> 00:06:50,960
 that's important for me.

118
00:06:50,960 --> 00:06:55,920
 'Cause what I'm gonna share today is absolutely what God is saying.

119
00:06:55,920 --> 00:06:57,760
 And we've discerned this as an eldership,

120
00:06:57,760 --> 00:07:00,000
 as a staff, as our pastors and leaders,

121
00:07:00,000 --> 00:07:01,280
 we've discerned this.

122
00:07:01,280 --> 00:07:04,240
 This is what God is saying to us as a corporate body,

123
00:07:04,240 --> 00:07:05,920
 as a community ourselves.

124
00:07:05,920 --> 00:07:08,480
 But it is also what I think God is saying to you.

125
00:07:08,480 --> 00:07:12,000
 And I think in 2026, by having to pull you more alive,

126
00:07:12,000 --> 00:07:12,800
 I'm gonna be sharing,

127
00:07:12,800 --> 00:07:15,760
 there's something in this that is specific to you.

128
00:07:15,760 --> 00:07:18,480
 No one is in this room, no one is online right now.

129
00:07:18,480 --> 00:07:19,840
 Hi to everybody online.

130
00:07:19,840 --> 00:07:21,360
 Nobody is in our overflow right now.

131
00:07:21,360 --> 00:07:22,640
 Hi to everybody in the overflow.

132
00:07:22,640 --> 00:07:24,480
 In fact, if you're in the overflow, can you wave right now at me?

133
00:07:24,480 --> 00:07:26,640
 Yeah, come on, do it.

134
00:07:26,640 --> 00:07:28,320
 I can see, yeah, I can't see you.

135
00:07:28,320 --> 00:07:30,480
 No, you're just waving, you're waving at a screen.

136
00:07:30,480 --> 00:07:31,360
 That's fine, that's good.

137
00:07:31,360 --> 00:07:34,080
 But I believe that no one's here by mistake.

138
00:07:34,080 --> 00:07:36,880
 So what I'm gonna say, something is significant for you.

139
00:07:36,880 --> 00:07:37,380
 Is that right?

140
00:07:37,380 --> 00:07:40,320
 Come on church, is that all right?

141
00:07:40,320 --> 00:07:41,680
 Can I pray?

142
00:07:41,680 --> 00:07:43,120
 Lord, just thank you so much

143
00:07:43,120 --> 00:07:45,200
 that we get to gather in a room like this,

144
00:07:45,200 --> 00:07:46,800
 gather in a city like this.

145
00:07:46,800 --> 00:07:48,240
 Lord, we love Hong Kong.

146
00:07:48,240 --> 00:07:52,560
 And that we get to hear your speaking voice to us.

147
00:07:52,560 --> 00:07:56,560
 Lord, without your vision, people perish.

148
00:07:58,080 --> 00:08:01,200
 But with your vision and your word, people come alive.

149
00:08:01,200 --> 00:08:04,960
 So Lord, I pray that as we open this up, we would come alive.

150
00:08:04,960 --> 00:08:08,160
 And that Lord, there would be something in this

151
00:08:08,160 --> 00:08:10,160
 that would grab a hold of our hearts

152
00:08:10,160 --> 00:08:12,560
 and that would move us to act.

153
00:08:12,560 --> 00:08:14,640
 And we thank you for this in Jesus' name.

154
00:08:14,640 --> 00:08:16,720
 Every one of us says, amen.

155
00:08:16,720 --> 00:08:20,560
 I think what's really important to know right up front

156
00:08:20,560 --> 00:08:23,600
 is that I am not bringing or releasing today a new vision.

157
00:08:23,600 --> 00:08:25,840
 Our vision has not changed here at the Vine.

158
00:08:25,840 --> 00:08:27,440
 It has not changed since 2013.

159
00:08:27,440 --> 00:08:30,240
 And our vision is the vision that God has given us.

160
00:08:30,240 --> 00:08:33,280
 And today is not about communicating to you a new vision.

161
00:08:33,280 --> 00:08:36,160
 What it is though, is communicating to you a new way

162
00:08:36,160 --> 00:08:39,520
 for us to understand the working of that vision

163
00:08:39,520 --> 00:08:41,120
 in this current season.

164
00:08:41,120 --> 00:08:44,880
 Back in 2013, a few months before I became senior pastor

165
00:08:44,880 --> 00:08:47,520
 here at the Vine, I took over from John and Tony

166
00:08:47,520 --> 00:08:48,880
 who had led this church so faithfully.

167
00:08:48,880 --> 00:08:50,240
 And I'm just, he's gonna hate me for this,

168
00:08:50,240 --> 00:08:52,000
 but Tony's sitting right here.

169
00:08:52,000 --> 00:08:54,960
 And he was one of our founding pastors at the Vine.

170
00:08:54,960 --> 00:08:57,280
 I think on Vision Sunday, it's always important

171
00:08:57,280 --> 00:08:59,600
 to honor and recognize.

172
00:08:59,600 --> 00:09:05,440
 And I know John and Sandra, our other two founding pastors

173
00:09:05,440 --> 00:09:06,800
 are watching online right now as well.

174
00:09:06,800 --> 00:09:07,760
 So we love you guys too.

175
00:09:07,760 --> 00:09:08,800
 And thank you for all that you do.

176
00:09:08,800 --> 00:09:11,600
 Can we give John and Sandra a round of applause as well.

177
00:09:11,600 --> 00:09:16,320
 God has been building for many years.

178
00:09:16,320 --> 00:09:19,440
 And so a few months prior to me taking over as senior pastor,

179
00:09:19,440 --> 00:09:21,600
 the Lord spoke to me about the vision He wanted for us

180
00:09:21,600 --> 00:09:22,800
 in this season.

181
00:09:22,800 --> 00:09:25,760
 And He said, "Andrew, I don't want you to grow a big church.

182
00:09:25,760 --> 00:09:27,040
 I want you to grow big people."

183
00:09:27,040 --> 00:09:29,040
 And so that is our vision.

184
00:09:29,040 --> 00:09:29,760
 It's three words.

185
00:09:29,760 --> 00:09:31,760
 Hopefully if you've been coming here, you've heard it before.

186
00:09:31,760 --> 00:09:33,600
 Growing big people.

187
00:09:33,600 --> 00:09:34,800
 Very simple, very easy.

188
00:09:34,800 --> 00:09:36,480
 You can very much remember that.

189
00:09:36,480 --> 00:09:38,240
 That is the vision of the Vine Church.

190
00:09:38,240 --> 00:09:41,520
 Not to grow a big church per se, but to grow big people.

191
00:09:41,520 --> 00:09:43,520
 And as God was speaking to me about this,

192
00:09:43,520 --> 00:09:45,680
 He took me to Ephesians chapter four

193
00:09:45,680 --> 00:09:49,840
 and to that glorious passage where Paul writes to his church

194
00:09:49,840 --> 00:09:52,240
 and says, "This is how Jesus matures us."

195
00:09:52,240 --> 00:09:58,160
 The idea of growing big people is the idea of maturing in Christ Jesus,

196
00:09:58,160 --> 00:09:59,280
 becoming more like Him.

197
00:09:59,280 --> 00:10:01,600
 So I want to read to you the founding passage

198
00:10:01,600 --> 00:10:05,120
 that we have as a church with this vision of growing big people.

199
00:10:05,120 --> 00:10:07,680
 It's from Ephesians four, starting in verse 11.

200
00:10:07,680 --> 00:10:10,720
 It says, "It was He who gave some to be apostles,

201
00:10:10,720 --> 00:10:13,200
 some to be prophets, some to be evangelists,

202
00:10:13,200 --> 00:10:14,800
 some to be pastors and teachers,

203
00:10:14,800 --> 00:10:18,160
 to prepare God's people for works of service,

204
00:10:18,160 --> 00:10:20,880
 so that the body of Christ may be built up

205
00:10:20,880 --> 00:10:24,000
 until we all reach unity in the faith

206
00:10:24,000 --> 00:10:26,400
 and in the knowledge of the Son of God."

207
00:10:26,400 --> 00:10:28,880
 And notice this, "And become mature,

208
00:10:28,880 --> 00:10:34,000
 attaining to the whole measure of the fullness of Christ."

209
00:10:34,000 --> 00:10:36,320
 This is what it means for us to grow big people here at the Vine.

210
00:10:36,320 --> 00:10:39,040
 And this is our vision passage.

211
00:10:39,040 --> 00:10:41,040
 I love what Paul says.

212
00:10:41,040 --> 00:10:42,960
 He says, "You want to know how exciting the church is?

213
00:10:42,960 --> 00:10:48,160
 It's like by His Spirit, God works in the people of an environment like this,

214
00:10:48,160 --> 00:10:51,200
 where they bring their gifts and they serve one another.

215
00:10:51,200 --> 00:10:52,880
 And through works of service,

216
00:10:52,880 --> 00:10:55,520
 there's unity in the knowledge of the Son of God.

217
00:10:55,520 --> 00:10:58,320
 And they grow in that and they become," Paul says, "mature."

218
00:10:58,320 --> 00:10:59,440
 And he defines it, he says,

219
00:10:59,440 --> 00:11:03,760
 "Attaining to the whole measure of the fullness of Jesus."

220
00:11:03,760 --> 00:11:07,120
 Our heart for you here at the Vine

221
00:11:07,120 --> 00:11:10,080
 is whether you're with us for two weeks, two months, two years, two decades,

222
00:11:10,080 --> 00:11:13,440
 is that during that period of time, you would have grown in Christ Jesus.

223
00:11:13,440 --> 00:11:17,040
 You would feel like you've reflect more of His character,

224
00:11:17,040 --> 00:11:20,320
 more of His heart, that you're living more sacrificially

225
00:11:20,320 --> 00:11:21,920
 to the things that He's called you to live on.

226
00:11:21,920 --> 00:11:26,560
 That you would feel more alive, more as you are created to be than ever before.

227
00:11:26,560 --> 00:11:30,160
 That's the whole point of why we gather here every week,

228
00:11:30,160 --> 00:11:32,960
 is that you would know in your lifetime

229
00:11:32,960 --> 00:11:37,200
 what it is to attain to the whole measure of the fullness of Jesus.

230
00:11:37,200 --> 00:11:38,800
 Now, that's our vision.

231
00:11:38,800 --> 00:11:40,320
 We've had that for a number of years.

232
00:11:40,320 --> 00:11:43,360
 And what God has done is He's opened that vision to us

233
00:11:43,360 --> 00:11:46,560
 in different ways of thinking about it over the last number of years.

234
00:11:46,560 --> 00:11:48,800
 I want to very quickly just show you this,

235
00:11:48,800 --> 00:11:52,640
 because I think it's important to honor the word that has been spoken before

236
00:11:52,640 --> 00:11:56,960
 and see how this now adds to the word that He's speaking today.

237
00:11:56,960 --> 00:11:59,680
 So when we first released this back in 2013,

238
00:11:59,680 --> 00:12:02,720
 from 2013 to 2016, in that period,

239
00:12:02,720 --> 00:12:06,160
 we had this thing called "Pathways of Maturity."

240
00:12:06,160 --> 00:12:08,880
 It was just our way of helping to explain to the church

241
00:12:08,880 --> 00:12:13,600
 that there are seven biblical pathways by which God matures His people.

242
00:12:13,600 --> 00:12:15,520
 And so for a number of years in that period,

243
00:12:15,520 --> 00:12:18,400
 we taught from the pulpit about what those pathways were,

244
00:12:18,400 --> 00:12:19,120
 and we called people.

245
00:12:19,120 --> 00:12:21,360
 Was anyone here for the Pathways of Maturity season?

246
00:12:21,360 --> 00:12:23,440
 Let me see your hands, raise them nice and high.

247
00:12:23,440 --> 00:12:25,360
 Come on. Okay, that's a number of you.

248
00:12:25,360 --> 00:12:27,120
 Do you feel like you're more like Jesus today?

249
00:12:27,120 --> 00:12:30,720
 You look like you're more like Jesus.

250
00:12:30,720 --> 00:12:31,920
 You're older, you're older.

251
00:12:31,920 --> 00:12:34,800
 That's part of it, part of it there, Richard.

252
00:12:34,800 --> 00:12:37,040
 So we taught you guys.

253
00:12:37,040 --> 00:12:38,080
 Now, here's the irony.

254
00:12:38,080 --> 00:12:41,200
 During that season, even though our focus was on discipleship

255
00:12:41,200 --> 00:12:44,480
 and explaining what growing big people in Ephesians 4 was all about,

256
00:12:44,480 --> 00:12:45,360
 here's what happened.

257
00:12:45,360 --> 00:12:46,320
 The church grew.

258
00:12:46,320 --> 00:12:48,880
 In fact, the church dramatically grew.

259
00:12:48,880 --> 00:12:51,040
 From about a thousand people in 2013,

260
00:12:51,040 --> 00:12:54,160
 we were about two and a half thousand people by the end of 2016.

261
00:12:54,160 --> 00:12:56,160
 So we had more than doubled in our growth,

262
00:12:56,160 --> 00:12:58,240
 even though God said, "Don't grow a big church, grow big people."

263
00:12:58,240 --> 00:12:59,120
 But it's funny, right?

264
00:12:59,120 --> 00:13:00,960
 You focus on your discipleship,

265
00:13:00,960 --> 00:13:02,480
 and people want to come and be a part of that.

266
00:13:02,480 --> 00:13:04,720
 But that created some challenge for us.

267
00:13:04,720 --> 00:13:07,680
 We realized that we were expanding more and more on Sundays,

268
00:13:07,680 --> 00:13:11,440
 but we were worried that we were growing breadth, but not depth.

269
00:13:11,440 --> 00:13:15,280
 And so the next season, God said, is "Call to Community."

270
00:13:15,280 --> 00:13:19,440
 So from 2017 to 2018, we spent a number of years telling the church,

271
00:13:19,440 --> 00:13:22,320
 "Your best discipleship and growth will not happen

272
00:13:22,320 --> 00:13:24,560
 when you gather for 90 minutes on a Sunday.

273
00:13:24,560 --> 00:13:26,960
 It's actually going to happen when you commit yourself

274
00:13:26,960 --> 00:13:30,640
 to a small group of people where you are known and you know them,

275
00:13:30,640 --> 00:13:33,840
 where you're doing life with them, you're accountable with them,

276
00:13:33,840 --> 00:13:36,000
 you have prayer together, you grow together.

277
00:13:36,000 --> 00:13:39,200
 Small community is where we grow the most."

278
00:13:39,200 --> 00:13:41,760
 And we still say this almost every week here at The Mind,

279
00:13:41,760 --> 00:13:44,880
 that this is not the be all and end all 90 minutes right now.

280
00:13:44,880 --> 00:13:48,640
 What really will help you dramatically change in Christ Jesus

281
00:13:48,640 --> 00:13:52,800
 is by committing yourself to walking with people who truly know you,

282
00:13:52,800 --> 00:13:55,760
 who understand your struggles, understand your sin,

283
00:13:55,760 --> 00:13:58,400
 know your brokenness, love you just the same,

284
00:13:58,400 --> 00:14:01,040
 pray for you, walk with you, and you're doing the same with them.

285
00:14:01,040 --> 00:14:04,000
 There is nothing more profound than the gift of community.

286
00:14:04,000 --> 00:14:06,080
 So for two years, we talked about that.

287
00:14:06,080 --> 00:14:07,840
 Then after that, here's the cool thing.

288
00:14:07,840 --> 00:14:11,360
 Just a few months before the protest movement in 2019,

289
00:14:11,360 --> 00:14:14,240
 in the summer of 2019, turned our city upside down.

290
00:14:14,240 --> 00:14:17,680
 And then in 2020, COVID turned the world upside down.

291
00:14:17,680 --> 00:14:20,400
 Just a few months before that, God came to us and said,

292
00:14:20,400 --> 00:14:22,720
 "You need to start thinking about church differently.

293
00:14:22,720 --> 00:14:26,640
 You need to start thinking about church, not as a building,

294
00:14:26,640 --> 00:14:32,160
 a one location thing, but as almost like a river flowing through Hong Kong.

295
00:14:32,160 --> 00:14:35,520
 And if you can shift your way of thinking about church

296
00:14:35,520 --> 00:14:39,680
 from being a gathering in a building to church being God's people

297
00:14:39,680 --> 00:14:42,160
 in spheres of influence all over the city,

298
00:14:42,160 --> 00:14:46,080
 taking the hope of the gospel and watering it in their spheres of influence,

299
00:14:46,080 --> 00:14:48,800
 that's what church really is," Jesus was saying.

300
00:14:48,800 --> 00:14:50,560
 And I want you, as you see the three things,

301
00:14:50,560 --> 00:14:53,760
 this was the river model in 2019-20, take a look at the screen.

302
00:14:53,760 --> 00:14:58,320
 As you see this, this is the progression of God's spoken word to us here at the Vine.

303
00:14:58,320 --> 00:15:02,400
 Mature in Jesus, do that through community,

304
00:15:02,400 --> 00:15:05,840
 and make sure you now understand that church should be different

305
00:15:05,840 --> 00:15:06,960
 than how you think of it.

306
00:15:06,960 --> 00:15:11,600
 Not one building, one location, I've got to go there to be a part of church,

307
00:15:11,600 --> 00:15:14,000
 but we are the church, the people.

308
00:15:14,000 --> 00:15:17,680
 And as we live out the faith of the gospel

309
00:15:17,680 --> 00:15:19,840
 in whatever sphere of influence He's placed us in,

310
00:15:19,840 --> 00:15:22,080
 that's where church takes place.

311
00:15:22,080 --> 00:15:25,200
 Now, it was so prophetic that God spoke that to us

312
00:15:25,200 --> 00:15:28,400
 just a few months before Hong Kong turned upside down,

313
00:15:28,400 --> 00:15:30,720
 and we weren't able to host services in this building

314
00:15:30,720 --> 00:15:34,080
 because of the protests that were happening just here in Wan Chai.

315
00:15:34,080 --> 00:15:39,040
 And then COVID came and global church got shut down for however long it was.

316
00:15:39,040 --> 00:15:40,960
 Isn't it amazing that we have a speaking God?

317
00:15:41,920 --> 00:15:42,640
 Come on, church.

318
00:15:42,640 --> 00:15:46,800
 Isn't it amazing that that prophetic voice prepared us

319
00:15:46,800 --> 00:15:48,480
 for what was about to take place?

320
00:15:48,480 --> 00:15:50,640
 So that was the next season.

321
00:15:50,640 --> 00:15:53,440
 And then just recently last year at Vision Sunday,

322
00:15:53,440 --> 00:15:56,720
 I stood before you all, and I said something that sounded very scary,

323
00:15:56,720 --> 00:15:58,400
 and to be honest, it's still scary today,

324
00:15:58,400 --> 00:16:03,680
 and that is that we're in a season that we're calling uncharted from 2025 onwards,

325
00:16:03,680 --> 00:16:06,560
 which is this idea that God is saying,

326
00:16:06,560 --> 00:16:08,720
 "Okay, I've told you to mature.

327
00:16:08,720 --> 00:16:10,320
 I've asked you to be in community.

328
00:16:10,320 --> 00:16:12,880
 I've redefined how you think about church.

329
00:16:12,880 --> 00:16:14,560
 Now you're ready for adventure."

330
00:16:14,560 --> 00:16:19,440
 Do you see how God works over many years to shape a church community?

331
00:16:19,440 --> 00:16:21,600
 He's like, "Now you're ready for adventure.

332
00:16:21,600 --> 00:16:23,360
 Now you're ready to really trust me.

333
00:16:23,360 --> 00:16:24,960
 Now you're ready to get out there."

334
00:16:24,960 --> 00:16:29,280
 The whole uncharted season we spoke about at Vision Sunday last year

335
00:16:29,280 --> 00:16:32,960
 is this idea that God has come and taken us out of our comfort zone,

336
00:16:32,960 --> 00:16:34,880
 that God has placed us.

337
00:16:34,880 --> 00:16:38,480
 The picture we had was like, we're out on uncharted waters.

338
00:16:39,040 --> 00:16:41,840
 We're literally somewhere where we no longer have a map

339
00:16:41,840 --> 00:16:44,160
 or a strategy for how we should be.

340
00:16:44,160 --> 00:16:47,120
 We have to completely trust that God is in control.

341
00:16:47,120 --> 00:16:51,520
 And I think as we see what happens in the Middle East overnight,

342
00:16:51,520 --> 00:16:55,600
 it just is another reminder to us that we're living in an uncharted time in our world,

343
00:16:55,600 --> 00:16:58,240
 that we are out of our comfort zone,

344
00:16:58,240 --> 00:16:59,600
 that we don't always have the answers,

345
00:16:59,600 --> 00:17:01,840
 that we don't always know what's going to happen next,

346
00:17:01,840 --> 00:17:04,880
 that things do get scary, that things are hard.

347
00:17:04,880 --> 00:17:06,720
 And Jesus is being saying to us,

348
00:17:06,720 --> 00:17:08,720
 "This is actually where I want my church.

349
00:17:08,720 --> 00:17:12,400
 I don't want my church to be in a safe bubble on a hill somewhere.

350
00:17:12,400 --> 00:17:15,760
 I want my church to be out in uncharted waters,

351
00:17:15,760 --> 00:17:19,040
 pioneering something new in the world today,

352
00:17:19,040 --> 00:17:21,760
 to be that hope in a time of crisis,

353
00:17:21,760 --> 00:17:24,880
 to be a place of love when everybody's talking about hate,

354
00:17:24,880 --> 00:17:27,840
 to actually show the world that there's another way to live

355
00:17:27,840 --> 00:17:30,320
 than the broken times that they're living in."

356
00:17:30,320 --> 00:17:31,840
 That's uncharted.

357
00:17:31,840 --> 00:17:34,000
 And that's where He wants us to be.

358
00:17:34,000 --> 00:17:37,120
 And I remember when I shared this to us last year and we talked about it,

359
00:17:37,120 --> 00:17:39,360
 I think all of us were like, "Really?"

360
00:17:39,360 --> 00:17:42,640
 Like we would prefer another time.

361
00:17:42,640 --> 00:17:44,480
 And I would love to stand before you today and say,

362
00:17:44,480 --> 00:17:46,080
 "Don't worry, uncharted's finished."

363
00:17:46,080 --> 00:17:49,040
 But unfortunately, I'm standing before you today and saying,

364
00:17:49,040 --> 00:17:52,880
 "We are just getting started, okay, in this time of uncharted."

365
00:17:52,880 --> 00:17:55,120
 And unfortunately, things didn't get even more uncomfortable

366
00:17:55,120 --> 00:17:55,920
 and even more messy.

367
00:17:55,920 --> 00:17:58,000
 And I'll tell you about that in a little moment.

368
00:17:58,000 --> 00:18:01,040
 But alongside of this season of uncharted,

369
00:18:01,040 --> 00:18:03,280
 we had a picture, didn't we, of a sailing ship.

370
00:18:03,280 --> 00:18:04,960
 We spoke about this last year.

371
00:18:04,960 --> 00:18:08,320
 And the sailing ship was this idea that the Vine is like this ship

372
00:18:08,320 --> 00:18:11,520
 that has gone out from safe harbor, from what we know,

373
00:18:11,520 --> 00:18:14,720
 out into this place of uncharted waters and uncharted times.

374
00:18:14,720 --> 00:18:16,000
 We don't have a map.

375
00:18:16,000 --> 00:18:17,280
 We don't have a strategy.

376
00:18:17,280 --> 00:18:18,560
 We don't know where we're going.

377
00:18:18,560 --> 00:18:22,560
 We're just going to have to trust that the captain on the ship

378
00:18:22,560 --> 00:18:24,160
 is leading us in the right direction.

379
00:18:24,160 --> 00:18:26,240
 And as we talked about that picture,

380
00:18:26,240 --> 00:18:28,240
 and we mentioned that picture a number of times last year,

381
00:18:28,240 --> 00:18:31,920
 many of you sent emails or spoke to our pastors or came up to us and said,

382
00:18:31,920 --> 00:18:34,000
 "I'm in a season of uncharted in my life."

383
00:18:34,000 --> 00:18:37,520
 You know, and I feel like I'm on that boat or that ship in uncharted waters.

384
00:18:37,520 --> 00:18:40,080
 And, you know, it's kind of scary, but it's exciting.

385
00:18:40,080 --> 00:18:41,440
 It's a season of adventure, blah, blah.

386
00:18:41,440 --> 00:18:43,200
 I know this resonated with many of you.

387
00:18:43,200 --> 00:18:48,320
 Well, towards the end of last year, I was just spending time praying and saying,

388
00:18:48,320 --> 00:18:51,120
 "God, what is really on your heart for this season of uncharted?

389
00:18:51,120 --> 00:18:53,040
 What is the next thing?"

390
00:18:53,040 --> 00:18:55,360
 And it was interesting because God, as He so often does,

391
00:18:55,360 --> 00:18:58,000
 often when He wants to tell me the next thing,

392
00:18:58,000 --> 00:19:01,360
 either in my own private life or here at the Vine, He tells me off.

393
00:19:01,360 --> 00:19:02,720
 You know, He sort of says,

394
00:19:02,720 --> 00:19:04,000
 "Here's something you need to remember.

395
00:19:04,000 --> 00:19:05,200
 Here's something that you haven't done right,

396
00:19:05,200 --> 00:19:06,960
 or here's something that you need to address."

397
00:19:06,960 --> 00:19:13,600
 And I saw a picture of the Vine as a ship, if you will, out on uncharted waters.

398
00:19:13,600 --> 00:19:16,320
 But as I saw it, as I was praying in this vision,

399
00:19:16,320 --> 00:19:20,880
 I could see that the ship was not sailing with purpose or intent.

400
00:19:20,880 --> 00:19:28,400
 Instead, the ship was moving around based on the waves that were hitting it

401
00:19:28,400 --> 00:19:32,400
 and the current of the water of the ocean and how it was moving it.

402
00:19:32,880 --> 00:19:36,240
 So in other words, as I saw this ship in uncharted waters,

403
00:19:36,240 --> 00:19:39,680
 it wasn't like the ship was sailing well in that space.

404
00:19:39,680 --> 00:19:42,160
 It felt like the ship was drifting,

405
00:19:42,160 --> 00:19:48,240
 what was kind of like moving around and pushed back by some of the waves

406
00:19:48,240 --> 00:19:49,200
 and some of the current.

407
00:19:49,200 --> 00:19:53,120
 And I saw this and I sensed God saying, "This is dangerous."

408
00:19:53,120 --> 00:19:58,160
 And one of the temptations in a time of uncharted as a church community

409
00:19:58,160 --> 00:20:02,320
 is to sort of think that because we can't have the map or strategy,

410
00:20:02,320 --> 00:20:05,440
 then everything's kind of like just nothing for us to do.

411
00:20:05,440 --> 00:20:07,520
 And we're just going to kind of sit there with our arms crossed.

412
00:20:07,520 --> 00:20:10,480
 If we do that, we end up drifting.

413
00:20:10,480 --> 00:20:14,400
 As I was praying and I saw this, I wrote something down

414
00:20:14,400 --> 00:20:16,080
 that I thought the Lord was saying to me,

415
00:20:16,080 --> 00:20:17,600
 but then I think he's saying it to us.

416
00:20:17,600 --> 00:20:18,880
 Let me read this to you.

417
00:20:18,880 --> 00:20:21,120
 This is from my diary that I wrote at that time.

418
00:20:21,120 --> 00:20:23,680
 I said, "Yes, this is an uncharted season."

419
00:20:23,680 --> 00:20:24,720
 This is Jesus speaking.

420
00:20:24,720 --> 00:20:26,800
 "Yes, you are to wait for my leading.

421
00:20:26,800 --> 00:20:29,840
 Yes, you are to go wherever it is that I decide to send you.

422
00:20:29,840 --> 00:20:33,840
 But that doesn't mean you have no responsibilities along the way.

423
00:20:33,840 --> 00:20:36,640
 It doesn't mean that you're mere passengers.

424
00:20:36,640 --> 00:20:39,760
 No, you're not passengers, you're sailors.

425
00:20:39,760 --> 00:20:41,920
 And it's time to set sail."

426
00:20:41,920 --> 00:20:44,160
 Oh, yeah.

427
00:20:44,160 --> 00:20:49,680
 Now, it sounds great, but I realized what the Lord was saying is,

428
00:20:49,680 --> 00:20:50,480
 "You're drifting.

429
00:20:50,480 --> 00:20:57,200
 You're kind of just going with the way that the waves are pushing you."

430
00:20:57,200 --> 00:21:00,160
 And as he began to speak this, and I was beginning to get excited,

431
00:21:00,160 --> 00:21:04,480
 he's like, "You've forgotten what was actually in that foundation scripture

432
00:21:04,480 --> 00:21:06,080
 I gave you for growing big people."

433
00:21:06,080 --> 00:21:07,440
 He's like, "Read it again."

434
00:21:07,440 --> 00:21:08,000
 And I did.

435
00:21:08,000 --> 00:21:10,240
 And as I read it, he said, "Keep reading."

436
00:21:10,240 --> 00:21:12,720
 So what I read to you earlier is up to verse 13.

437
00:21:12,720 --> 00:21:14,560
 Let me now read you verse 14,

438
00:21:14,560 --> 00:21:17,040
 which is the next verse, funnily enough, straight after it.

439
00:21:17,040 --> 00:21:19,200
 It says this, "Then," Paul says,

440
00:21:19,200 --> 00:21:24,080
 "we will no longer be infants tossed back and forth by the waves,

441
00:21:24,960 --> 00:21:28,240
 blown here and there by every wind of teaching

442
00:21:28,240 --> 00:21:33,200
 and the cunning and craftiness of people in their deceitful scheming."

443
00:21:33,200 --> 00:21:35,520
 It's funny to me that after Paul says,

444
00:21:35,520 --> 00:21:37,440
 "This is what it means to grow big people.

445
00:21:37,440 --> 00:21:40,480
 Do all of these things so that you can attain to the whole measure,

446
00:21:40,480 --> 00:21:41,440
 the wholeness of Christ."

447
00:21:41,440 --> 00:21:44,080
 He's saying, "If you don't, then here's what happens.

448
00:21:44,080 --> 00:21:45,200
 You're just going to drift.

449
00:21:45,200 --> 00:21:51,200
 The waves and the ocean current is going to be what moves you.

450
00:21:52,160 --> 00:21:55,840
 It's going to be like there's these forces working against you."

451
00:21:55,840 --> 00:21:57,680
 It's interesting that in the Old Testament,

452
00:21:57,680 --> 00:22:02,720
 when the Old Testament speaks about this idea of sin and evil

453
00:22:02,720 --> 00:22:06,960
 and evil forces in the world, it uses imagery of the ocean.

454
00:22:06,960 --> 00:22:09,920
 It's one of the most profound things.

455
00:22:09,920 --> 00:22:12,320
 Can you hear it?

456
00:22:12,320 --> 00:22:16,800
 Can you imagine what it's like?

457
00:22:16,800 --> 00:22:17,920
 Okay, take a minute for a moment.

458
00:22:17,920 --> 00:22:18,400
 Close your eyes.

459
00:22:18,400 --> 00:22:19,120
 I want you to close your eyes.

460
00:22:19,120 --> 00:22:20,320
 Can you close your eyes on me?

461
00:22:20,320 --> 00:22:22,560
 Oh yeah, you didn't expect this when you came to church today.

462
00:22:22,560 --> 00:22:23,060
 That's okay.

463
00:22:23,060 --> 00:22:24,960
 You're on the ship.

464
00:22:24,960 --> 00:22:28,960
 The wind is howling.

465
00:22:28,960 --> 00:22:34,560
 But the ship is not catching the wind.

466
00:22:34,560 --> 00:22:41,760
 And instead, it's being buffeted by the waves and by the current of the ocean.

467
00:22:41,760 --> 00:22:44,000
 And it is drifting.

468
00:22:44,000 --> 00:22:47,760
 Okay, open your eyes again.

469
00:22:48,640 --> 00:22:56,960
 If we're not really careful, we will be in a situation where, yes, we're in uncharted waters.

470
00:22:56,960 --> 00:23:03,120
 But the direction we're heading is being defined for us more by what the world is trying to say to us,

471
00:23:03,120 --> 00:23:08,720
 by sin and darkness and evil, than what the Word of God is speaking into us.

472
00:23:08,720 --> 00:23:14,320
 And as I was wrestling with this idea, I could come to understand that this is what God is saying.

473
00:23:14,320 --> 00:23:15,280
 He's like, "Hey, come on."

474
00:23:15,920 --> 00:23:20,800
 He's like, "I'm at work here. I'm doing things. I'm at work."

475
00:23:20,800 --> 00:23:25,680
 But you've got to be careful that you don't just end up drifting and staying immature.

476
00:23:25,680 --> 00:23:26,560
 Let me say it this way.

477
00:23:26,560 --> 00:23:30,960
 To be immature is to drift on the currents of the ocean.

478
00:23:30,960 --> 00:23:33,600
 To be mature is to catch the wind.

479
00:23:33,600 --> 00:23:35,280
 Are you following this?

480
00:23:35,280 --> 00:23:37,600
 And this is what Paul's saying to the church.

481
00:23:37,600 --> 00:23:39,920
 He's like, "Here's how you stay in immaturity.

482
00:23:39,920 --> 00:23:44,160
 You just allow the waves and the currents of the world to define you and shape you.

483
00:23:44,160 --> 00:23:47,840
 Here's how you move forward in purpose and intent.

484
00:23:47,840 --> 00:23:52,960
 Even if you don't know the direction you're going, it is not for you to know the direction.

485
00:23:52,960 --> 00:23:53,920
 That's for me.

486
00:23:53,920 --> 00:23:56,480
 But your job is to catch the wind.

487
00:23:56,480 --> 00:24:00,880
 Your job is to put up your sails.

488
00:24:00,880 --> 00:24:04,480
 Your job is to be a sailor.

489
00:24:04,480 --> 00:24:07,040
 It is time to set sail.

490
00:24:07,040 --> 00:24:12,640
 It's funny because I was at a memorial service back in January.

491
00:24:12,640 --> 00:24:16,560
 And as I was sitting in this memorial service, I looked to my right and lo and behold,

492
00:24:16,560 --> 00:24:18,480
 I was sitting next to Jackie Pullinger.

493
00:24:18,480 --> 00:24:21,040
 So Jackie may be well known to a number of you.

494
00:24:21,040 --> 00:24:23,680
 She's a good friend here of the Vine, which has been amazing.

495
00:24:23,680 --> 00:24:29,120
 Jackie's been a missionary, really, a pastor and leader to our city for 60 years.

496
00:24:29,120 --> 00:24:33,520
 Originally called as a young woman to come and serve in the walled city in Kowloon,

497
00:24:33,520 --> 00:24:39,360
 working with drug addicts, helping drug addicts come off drugs through the power of prayer.

498
00:24:39,360 --> 00:24:42,160
 And she's built a ministry around that for 60 years.

499
00:24:42,160 --> 00:24:46,880
 She's still here in Hong Kong now in her 80s, still doing the work,

500
00:24:46,880 --> 00:24:53,520
 working with drug addicts, praying for them and helping them to come off of drug addiction here in Hong Kong.

501
00:24:53,520 --> 00:24:55,760
 I was sitting next to her and we were just chatting together.

502
00:24:55,760 --> 00:24:58,400
 And she leans over to me at one point before the service starts.

503
00:24:58,400 --> 00:25:01,520
 And she goes, Andrew, have I told you about my sailing club?

504
00:25:01,520 --> 00:25:05,520
 And I thought, this is funny.

505
00:25:05,520 --> 00:25:10,800
 I mean, I literally was like, this is funny because I was imagining this lovely 80 year old woman

506
00:25:10,800 --> 00:25:15,520
 and a bunch of heroin addicts out on these boats in Hong Kong somewhere.

507
00:25:15,520 --> 00:25:16,560
 And I'm like, really?

508
00:25:16,560 --> 00:25:19,440
 Like, that's a picture, right?

509
00:25:19,440 --> 00:25:25,520
 And I said to her, like, you mean like sailing, like you're taking the boys out on these boats?

510
00:25:25,520 --> 00:25:27,120
 She's like, oh, no, no, no, no, no.

511
00:25:27,120 --> 00:25:29,040
 She's like, I'm not interested in yachts, Andrew.

512
00:25:29,040 --> 00:25:33,920
 She said, no, no, no, I'm teaching them to catch the wind of the spirit.

513
00:25:33,920 --> 00:25:38,160
 She's saying, I'm teaching my boys how to be sailors.

514
00:25:38,160 --> 00:25:42,880
 And she's like this, she's like, the wind of God's spirit is blowing all around.

515
00:25:42,880 --> 00:25:45,200
 It's time for us to catch it, she said.

516
00:25:45,200 --> 00:25:49,040
 And I'm like, this is exactly what the Holy Spirit is saying to us.

517
00:25:49,040 --> 00:25:53,440
 It's so cool how when God speaks, He doesn't speak to one person or one church,

518
00:25:53,440 --> 00:25:56,000
 but He has a unified voice in the church of God.

519
00:25:56,000 --> 00:25:58,320
 And as she's saying this to me, I'm feeling my heart beating

520
00:25:58,320 --> 00:26:01,440
 because God is saying exactly the same thing to us at that time.

521
00:26:01,440 --> 00:26:05,680
 And she's so excited because, and she says this, she's like, we don't have a wind problem.

522
00:26:06,800 --> 00:26:08,560
 Some of us have wind problems, so we're not going to go there.

523
00:26:08,560 --> 00:26:11,680
 Okay, so she said, we don't have a wind problem.

524
00:26:11,680 --> 00:26:13,440
 In other words, God is at work.

525
00:26:13,440 --> 00:26:15,200
 The issue is not the wind.

526
00:26:15,200 --> 00:26:17,280
 The issue is, do we have enough sailors?

527
00:26:17,280 --> 00:26:21,200
 Jesus said it this way, didn't He?

528
00:26:21,200 --> 00:26:25,600
 He said, the harvest is plentiful, but the harvesters are few.

529
00:26:25,600 --> 00:26:34,400
 I don't know if you've noticed this, but I believe that we're in a season

530
00:26:34,400 --> 00:26:37,520
 where the Holy Spirit is blowing on the world more than ever before.

531
00:26:37,520 --> 00:26:40,720
 I don't know if you've seen some of the amazing things that are happening.

532
00:26:40,720 --> 00:26:42,560
 You follow it on social media, you might be picking up

533
00:26:42,560 --> 00:26:45,280
 in the various Christian kind of networks that you have,

534
00:26:45,280 --> 00:26:47,200
 but we're seeing God's Spirit at work.

535
00:26:47,200 --> 00:26:50,080
 We're seeing this quiet revival happening in the UK,

536
00:26:50,080 --> 00:26:52,800
 where young people are coming back to Jesus

537
00:26:52,800 --> 00:26:56,240
 and flooding back into the church like never before.

538
00:26:56,240 --> 00:27:00,880
 We're seeing what we saw in Asbury University in Kentucky a few years ago,

539
00:27:00,880 --> 00:27:03,760
 more recently in Southeastern University in Florida.

540
00:27:03,760 --> 00:27:07,360
 But we're also seeing the Spirit moving here in Asia.

541
00:27:07,360 --> 00:27:09,520
 Churches growing, God doing stuff.

542
00:27:09,520 --> 00:27:11,840
 It is an incredibly exciting season.

543
00:27:11,840 --> 00:27:15,120
 And people are talking about, like, we're on the cusp of revival.

544
00:27:15,120 --> 00:27:18,720
 And I'm like, yeah, that's exciting, because we see it happening in other places.

545
00:27:18,720 --> 00:27:20,720
 But I'm like, I think it's actually happening here.

546
00:27:20,720 --> 00:27:24,000
 Like, I think the Holy Spirit is happening here.

547
00:27:24,000 --> 00:27:26,400
 I think the wind of the Spirit is blowing here.

548
00:27:26,400 --> 00:27:29,680
 And I think the excitement for us in the season that we're in,

549
00:27:29,680 --> 00:27:33,600
 in this Uncharted, is not to allow the waves and the current to drift us.

550
00:27:33,600 --> 00:27:34,720
 Wherever it wants.

551
00:27:34,720 --> 00:27:36,720
 No, there's purpose and intent.

552
00:27:36,720 --> 00:27:39,760
 We put up the sails to catch the wind that's already blowing.

553
00:27:39,760 --> 00:27:45,280
 G. Campbell Morgan, one of the great writers on revival,

554
00:27:45,280 --> 00:27:46,720
 he wrote this, and I read this the other day.

555
00:27:46,720 --> 00:27:47,600
 I want to read this to you.

556
00:27:47,600 --> 00:27:49,840
 He said, "We cannot organize revival,

557
00:27:49,840 --> 00:27:53,120
 but we can set our sails to catch the wind from heaven

558
00:27:53,120 --> 00:27:55,600
 when God chooses to blow upon His people again."

559
00:27:55,600 --> 00:27:59,840
 I think God is choosing to blow upon His people here at the Vine.

560
00:28:01,760 --> 00:28:02,720
 I'm going to say that one more time,

561
00:28:02,720 --> 00:28:04,640
 because that did not get the reaction I was hoping for.

562
00:28:04,640 --> 00:28:08,000
 I believe God's wind of the Spirit is blowing on you.

563
00:28:08,000 --> 00:28:10,420
 Yeah.

564
00:28:10,420 --> 00:28:15,840
 And I believe we're being invited into a season to put up our sails.

565
00:28:15,840 --> 00:28:18,720
 And what we've been doing as a leadership over the last few months,

566
00:28:18,720 --> 00:28:23,120
 our elders, our senior leadership team, our pastoral team, our staff,

567
00:28:23,120 --> 00:28:25,680
 we've been praying and saying, "God, okay, we get the picture.

568
00:28:25,680 --> 00:28:26,960
 You're blowing.

569
00:28:26,960 --> 00:28:28,800
 You're at work.

570
00:28:28,800 --> 00:28:30,320
 We don't want to drift.

571
00:28:30,320 --> 00:28:31,920
 What are the sails that we need to put up?"

572
00:28:31,920 --> 00:28:34,560
 And so what I want to do now for the rest of our time together

573
00:28:34,560 --> 00:28:35,920
 is just tell you about these sails.

574
00:28:35,920 --> 00:28:39,920
 There's four of them that we feel the Lord is inviting the Vine to lean into,

575
00:28:39,920 --> 00:28:41,680
 to put up in this season.

576
00:28:41,680 --> 00:28:43,760
 And as we do this, though,

577
00:28:43,760 --> 00:28:47,280
 this is not just for the Vine as a church corporately.

578
00:28:47,280 --> 00:28:50,000
 This is for you individually, like I said earlier.

579
00:28:50,000 --> 00:28:51,280
 So I think what the Lord is saying,

580
00:28:51,280 --> 00:28:53,840
 "Hey, put these sails up to catch the Spirit

581
00:28:53,840 --> 00:28:56,160
 of what I'm doing here at the Vine in this season

582
00:28:56,160 --> 00:29:00,000
 are the sails that I want to invite you to think about putting up in your life

583
00:29:00,880 --> 00:29:03,600
 to move in the direction that He has for you

584
00:29:03,600 --> 00:29:06,960
 and for you to come truly, fully alive."

585
00:29:06,960 --> 00:29:08,000
 Here's the important thing.

586
00:29:08,000 --> 00:29:09,760
 We cannot direct the wind.

587
00:29:09,760 --> 00:29:10,640
 Amen.

588
00:29:10,640 --> 00:29:11,600
 That's uncharted.

589
00:29:11,600 --> 00:29:13,680
 That's not our responsibility.

590
00:29:13,680 --> 00:29:15,040
 That's God's responsibility.

591
00:29:15,040 --> 00:29:18,720
 We cannot direct the wind, but we can adjust our sails.

592
00:29:18,720 --> 00:29:23,440
 And so I want to tell you about the sails that we're adjusting.

593
00:29:23,440 --> 00:29:23,840
 Are you ready?

594
00:29:23,840 --> 00:29:24,400
 Excited?

595
00:29:24,400 --> 00:29:25,280
 All right.

596
00:29:25,280 --> 00:29:26,160
 Here's the first one.

597
00:29:26,160 --> 00:29:29,040
 We feel that Lord is saying this.

598
00:29:29,040 --> 00:29:34,000
 The first thing that we must put up, the sail that we must put up

599
00:29:34,000 --> 00:29:38,240
 to catch the wind that is blowing is this beautiful idea

600
00:29:38,240 --> 00:29:40,800
 and sail of the presence of the Holy Spirit.

601
00:29:40,800 --> 00:29:42,020
 Isn't that cool?

602
00:29:42,020 --> 00:29:46,240
 See, the presence of the Holy Spirit is blowing upon us.

603
00:29:46,240 --> 00:29:49,360
 And we're in a season at the moment where we believe

604
00:29:49,360 --> 00:29:52,160
 that the Spirit of God is working here at the Vine like never before.

605
00:29:52,160 --> 00:29:54,240
 I don't know if you felt it as you come in on Sundays,

606
00:29:54,240 --> 00:29:56,000
 but there's something different happening amongst us.

607
00:29:56,000 --> 00:29:56,500
 Amen.

608
00:29:56,500 --> 00:29:58,880
 There's something significant taking place.

609
00:29:58,880 --> 00:30:01,360
 When we gather and we sing, but it's not just happening here.

610
00:30:01,360 --> 00:30:04,640
 It's happening across our different ministries and across our different places,

611
00:30:04,640 --> 00:30:08,480
 our different ways that we express church and community here at the Vine.

612
00:30:08,480 --> 00:30:11,680
 There's something significant that's happening with the wind of the Spirit,

613
00:30:11,680 --> 00:30:15,680
 the presence of God to heal and transform and to renew.

614
00:30:15,680 --> 00:30:18,000
 And one of the things that we sense as a leadership is

615
00:30:18,000 --> 00:30:21,360
 we got to put up the sail to catch the wind that is blowing.

616
00:30:21,360 --> 00:30:25,680
 There is nothing more sad than the Spirit at work in a church

617
00:30:25,680 --> 00:30:29,200
 when the church is actively pushing against the work of that Spirit.

618
00:30:29,200 --> 00:30:35,680
 And how do we position ourselves with our sails to catch that wind?

619
00:30:35,680 --> 00:30:38,960
 Well, it's going to require something that is going to be difficult for all of us.

620
00:30:38,960 --> 00:30:44,560
 It's going to require us to prioritize His presence by slowing down.

621
00:30:44,560 --> 00:30:46,660
 Say that again.

622
00:30:46,660 --> 00:30:50,800
 It's going to require prioritization of His presence to slow down.

623
00:30:50,800 --> 00:30:55,360
 As we make more room and more time for the Holy Spirit,

624
00:30:55,360 --> 00:30:57,760
 He will transform your life.

625
00:30:57,760 --> 00:31:02,000
 As you take more time and more room for the Holy Spirit,

626
00:31:02,000 --> 00:31:03,440
 He will transform your life.

627
00:31:03,440 --> 00:31:06,880
 And we are going to therefore reshape how we gather,

628
00:31:06,880 --> 00:31:10,560
 reshape our services, reshape our ministries

629
00:31:10,560 --> 00:31:14,640
 so that we're making intentional time to listen, receive,

630
00:31:14,640 --> 00:31:17,600
 and respond to the work of the Holy Spirit amongst us.

631
00:31:17,600 --> 00:31:20,640
 And that's going to require you to slow down

632
00:31:20,640 --> 00:31:23,040
 to receive what the Spirit is saying to you.

633
00:31:24,320 --> 00:31:25,680
 One of the things that I want to say,

634
00:31:25,680 --> 00:31:28,240
 and I'm going to say it boldly, and I'm not going to apologize for it.

635
00:31:28,240 --> 00:31:31,840
 One of the things that has frustrated me over the last year here at The Vine

636
00:31:31,840 --> 00:31:34,160
 is that so often when I'm preaching on a Sunday,

637
00:31:34,160 --> 00:31:37,920
 the very last word I might say in my sermon as I pray is "Amen."

638
00:31:37,920 --> 00:31:40,400
 And I can't tell you how many of you then stand up and leave.

639
00:31:40,400 --> 00:31:43,680
 Let me just say this.

640
00:31:43,680 --> 00:31:47,840
 It is going to require you to slow down to catch the Holy Spirit.

641
00:31:47,840 --> 00:31:51,680
 The most important thing that happens here at The Vine

642
00:31:51,680 --> 00:31:54,080
 is not the worship, and it is not what I say.

643
00:31:54,640 --> 00:31:58,720
 The most important thing is what God wants to say to you.

644
00:31:58,720 --> 00:32:01,760
 And that can happen in the sermon, and that can happen in the worship,

645
00:32:01,760 --> 00:32:03,120
 and it does, and it's awesome.

646
00:32:03,120 --> 00:32:05,680
 But we are going to be making space at the end.

647
00:32:05,680 --> 00:32:09,360
 The worship and the sermon move us to a place where we can receive.

648
00:32:09,360 --> 00:32:12,000
 And I want to say that we need a culture here at The Vine

649
00:32:12,000 --> 00:32:15,440
 of slowing down to receive what the Holy Spirit has to say.

650
00:32:15,440 --> 00:32:20,080
 And I want to invite you to consider your role in that.

651
00:32:20,080 --> 00:32:21,760
 I understand sometimes we have to leave.

652
00:32:21,760 --> 00:32:23,200
 There's appointments, there's kids.

653
00:32:23,200 --> 00:32:24,240
 I get it.

654
00:32:24,240 --> 00:32:26,720
 But I think we've got a bit too much of a culture right now

655
00:32:26,720 --> 00:32:30,320
 where we think the most important thing is the thing that the pastor says.

656
00:32:30,320 --> 00:32:33,680
 The most important thing is what Jesus wants to say to you.

657
00:32:33,680 --> 00:32:37,760
 And opening your heart to that and slowing down to receive it

658
00:32:37,760 --> 00:32:39,920
 will change your life.

659
00:32:39,920 --> 00:32:42,800
 Nothing I will say will ever change your life.

660
00:32:42,800 --> 00:32:47,200
 I hope what I say will inspire you

661
00:32:47,200 --> 00:32:49,280
 and open your heart to what Jesus wants to say to you.

662
00:32:49,280 --> 00:32:51,680
 That's the role that I have as a preacher and pastor,

663
00:32:51,680 --> 00:32:54,400
 is to lead you into a deeper encounter with Jesus.

664
00:32:54,400 --> 00:32:55,840
 But I will never change you.

665
00:32:55,840 --> 00:32:57,120
 Only Jesus will change you.

666
00:32:57,120 --> 00:33:02,640
 So we need to prioritize space for Jesus to truly minister.

667
00:33:02,640 --> 00:33:03,140
 Helpful?

668
00:33:03,140 --> 00:33:05,120
 That's the first one.

669
00:33:05,120 --> 00:33:05,920
 Here's the second one.

670
00:33:05,920 --> 00:33:08,640
 The second one that we're going to put up

671
00:33:08,640 --> 00:33:14,000
 is the sale of radical discipleship.

672
00:33:14,000 --> 00:33:16,880
 Now, this is really exciting.

673
00:33:16,880 --> 00:33:18,880
 And I want you to see how this flows

674
00:33:18,880 --> 00:33:20,880
 and all of this begins to build on each other.

675
00:33:20,880 --> 00:33:25,040
 So as we lean into more of the work of the Holy Spirit in our lives,

676
00:33:25,040 --> 00:33:29,200
 whenever there is a season of greater encounter with the Holy Spirit

677
00:33:29,200 --> 00:33:33,040
 that is always followed by a call to deeper and more radical discipleship.

678
00:33:33,040 --> 00:33:34,560
 Come on, church.

679
00:33:34,560 --> 00:33:38,560
 Whenever this takes place and you make space for this in your life,

680
00:33:38,560 --> 00:33:40,240
 you will be transformed.

681
00:33:40,240 --> 00:33:41,280
 You will be renewed.

682
00:33:41,280 --> 00:33:43,760
 You will be deeper in your commitment to Jesus.

683
00:33:43,760 --> 00:33:46,160
 You will have more of His character at work in your life.

684
00:33:46,160 --> 00:33:49,040
 The fruit of the Spirit will be shown more in your life.

685
00:33:49,040 --> 00:33:52,160
 Love, joy, peace, patience, kindness, goodness, faithfulness, gentleness, self-control

686
00:33:52,160 --> 00:33:55,520
 will burn up into your life as the Spirit moves.

687
00:33:55,520 --> 00:34:00,880
 And as you allow yourself to be changed and transformed by that Spirit, you will grow.

688
00:34:00,880 --> 00:34:06,000
 Radical discipleship is to recognize that not only is it,

689
00:34:06,000 --> 00:34:10,000
 I want more of the Spirit, it's also the Spirit saying, I want more of you.

690
00:34:10,000 --> 00:34:11,840
 Come on, church.

691
00:34:11,840 --> 00:34:14,880
 It's not just us saying, I want more of the Spirit.

692
00:34:14,880 --> 00:34:16,480
 It's God saying, okay, great.

693
00:34:16,480 --> 00:34:18,560
 Here's my Spirit so that you would change.

694
00:34:18,560 --> 00:34:19,280
 You would transform.

695
00:34:19,280 --> 00:34:20,000
 You would be refined.

696
00:34:20,000 --> 00:34:20,640
 You would repent.

697
00:34:20,640 --> 00:34:21,680
 You would be convicted.

698
00:34:21,680 --> 00:34:27,440
 You would have a movement in your life where my Spirit changes you, roughs out your edges.

699
00:34:27,440 --> 00:34:32,080
 You become more compassionate, more loving, more serving, more hopeful, more the person.

700
00:34:32,080 --> 00:34:35,120
 I want you to be in the Spirit of influence that I've placed you in.

701
00:34:35,120 --> 00:34:36,160
 That's discipleship.

702
00:34:36,160 --> 00:34:42,000
 It's not just becoming more like Jesus, but in becoming more like Jesus,

703
00:34:42,000 --> 00:34:44,480
 we become more of Jesus in the world.

704
00:34:44,480 --> 00:34:48,480
 Changing and transforming the Spirit of influence that He places in.

705
00:34:48,480 --> 00:34:49,520
 This is important.

706
00:34:49,520 --> 00:34:54,000
 So one of the things as a leadership, as we prayed and talked about this sale,

707
00:34:54,000 --> 00:34:58,320
 is we've sensed God say, look, you've told the church that we're growing big people.

708
00:34:58,320 --> 00:35:04,320
 Now tell them the commitments you're looking for to shape that discipleship within the church.

709
00:35:04,320 --> 00:35:07,680
 So we came up with these things called the guiding principles.

710
00:35:07,680 --> 00:35:10,160
 You're going to hear a lot more about this in the weeks and months ahead.

711
00:35:10,160 --> 00:35:14,240
 In fact, I'm going to be teaching next week specifically on these guiding principles.

712
00:35:14,240 --> 00:35:16,960
 But let me read to you what we're sensing.

713
00:35:16,960 --> 00:35:21,440
 So the Vine Church is a community of people on a journey together to become more like Jesus.

714
00:35:21,440 --> 00:35:23,600
 That's our vision, growing big people.

715
00:35:23,600 --> 00:35:28,240
 Our goal, notice this, is not to be perfect in achievement, but purposeful in pursuit.

716
00:35:28,240 --> 00:35:29,120
 Can I have an amen?

717
00:35:29,120 --> 00:35:33,360
 We are serious about maturing in Christ and expanding His kingdom.

718
00:35:33,360 --> 00:35:36,720
 And we understand that this is a gracious work of the Holy Spirit.

719
00:35:36,720 --> 00:35:38,240
 It's not our effort.

720
00:35:38,240 --> 00:35:39,760
 It is the work of the Spirit.

721
00:35:39,760 --> 00:35:41,680
 But we open ourselves to that work.

722
00:35:41,680 --> 00:35:46,000
 In our community, we walk with the Spirit by embracing a lifestyle

723
00:35:46,000 --> 00:35:48,400
 centered on the following commitments.

724
00:35:48,400 --> 00:35:51,040
 And we've said that there are five things we feel,

725
00:35:51,040 --> 00:35:54,800
 if we want to grow in Christ Jesus in the season we're in right now,

726
00:35:54,800 --> 00:35:56,000
 these five things are important.

727
00:35:56,000 --> 00:35:58,080
 Number one, surrendered to Scripture.

728
00:35:58,080 --> 00:36:02,800
 Not just people who read Scripture, as important as that is,

729
00:36:02,800 --> 00:36:05,840
 but be surrendered to Scripture.

730
00:36:05,840 --> 00:36:09,120
 Allow the Word of God to be the ultimate driving force,

731
00:36:09,120 --> 00:36:11,520
 the ultimate compass in our lives.

732
00:36:11,520 --> 00:36:12,720
 Surrender to Scripture.

733
00:36:12,720 --> 00:36:14,560
 Secondly, priority of presence.

734
00:36:15,680 --> 00:36:17,440
 This is these two things right here.

735
00:36:17,440 --> 00:36:20,720
 Surrender to Scripture, priority of presence.

736
00:36:20,720 --> 00:36:23,440
 Making that presence known and felt in our lives.

737
00:36:23,440 --> 00:36:25,920
 Number three, centered on Jesus.

738
00:36:25,920 --> 00:36:29,200
 We are nothing other than followers and believers in Jesus.

739
00:36:29,200 --> 00:36:32,800
 When Jesus said, "Deny yourself, pick up your cross and come after me."

740
00:36:32,800 --> 00:36:35,760
 He was literally saying, "Center yourself on me."

741
00:36:35,760 --> 00:36:39,360
 And whenever churches drift from the centrality of Jesus,

742
00:36:39,360 --> 00:36:42,160
 they become very dangerous, manipulative places.

743
00:36:43,280 --> 00:36:45,520
 Churches have to stay centered on Jesus.

744
00:36:45,520 --> 00:36:48,080
 Believers in Jesus have to stay centered on Jesus.

745
00:36:48,080 --> 00:36:51,440
 And when we drift, we become the worst versions of ourselves.

746
00:36:51,440 --> 00:36:54,240
 So Jesus is the priority.

747
00:36:54,240 --> 00:36:56,240
 Then, focused on renewal.

748
00:36:56,240 --> 00:36:59,040
 I love this thought of the fact that we are called as Christians

749
00:36:59,040 --> 00:37:00,320
 to renew the world around us.

750
00:37:00,320 --> 00:37:02,640
 We're to be focused on renewal.

751
00:37:02,640 --> 00:37:05,360
 That is to see the kingdom of God come in our spheres of influence,

752
00:37:05,360 --> 00:37:09,600
 in our workplace, in our schools, in our environments, in our families.

753
00:37:09,600 --> 00:37:10,560
 That's what we want.

754
00:37:10,560 --> 00:37:13,440
 And then finally, and this is perhaps one of the most key,

755
00:37:13,440 --> 00:37:15,040
 is rooted in relationship.

756
00:37:15,040 --> 00:37:17,520
 We do this by being in relationship with one another.

757
00:37:17,520 --> 00:37:20,640
 Not separate from one another, not our own saviors.

758
00:37:20,640 --> 00:37:22,560
 We're rooted in Christ, centered in Him.

759
00:37:22,560 --> 00:37:25,200
 We're working together, rooted in relationship together.

760
00:37:25,200 --> 00:37:27,680
 These five things you're going to be hearing a lot more about

761
00:37:27,680 --> 00:37:32,240
 over the years ahead are going to reshape a lot of how we do our ministries here,

762
00:37:32,240 --> 00:37:33,760
 a lot of how we teach here,

763
00:37:33,760 --> 00:37:37,520
 a lot of how we begin to put these cells up to catch the wind.

764
00:37:37,520 --> 00:37:38,960
 Is this helpful for you so far?

765
00:37:38,960 --> 00:37:39,600
 Everybody okay?

766
00:37:40,160 --> 00:37:42,000
 All right, let me give you the final two.

767
00:37:42,000 --> 00:37:42,560
 Here's one.

768
00:37:42,560 --> 00:37:46,960
 This is, and this flows nicely on again from the others.

769
00:37:46,960 --> 00:37:51,280
 This is the sale of bearing witness.

770
00:37:51,280 --> 00:37:53,760
 We're calling it bearing witness.

771
00:37:53,760 --> 00:37:56,240
 Now this is a great, by the way,

772
00:37:56,240 --> 00:37:58,400
 how awesome is all the design that are on these cells?

773
00:37:58,400 --> 00:38:01,520
 This is our creative team, Balana actually did these designs

774
00:38:01,520 --> 00:38:03,200
 and our creative team have done all this.

775
00:38:03,200 --> 00:38:04,000
 I love it, I love it.

776
00:38:04,000 --> 00:38:07,440
 Now follow with me, church, follow with me.

777
00:38:07,440 --> 00:38:10,720
 More of the Holy Spirit transforming and changing us.

778
00:38:10,720 --> 00:38:14,240
 But if all we do is stop on this side of the ship,

779
00:38:14,240 --> 00:38:19,200
 all we're going to do then is be a really cool bless me club in a building.

780
00:38:19,200 --> 00:38:20,240
 Are you with me?

781
00:38:20,240 --> 00:38:22,160
 We have to shift to bear witness.

782
00:38:22,160 --> 00:38:26,160
 This draws from the idea of Acts chapter one, verse eight,

783
00:38:26,160 --> 00:38:30,800
 where Jesus says, "Power will come upon you when you receive my spirit

784
00:38:30,800 --> 00:38:35,040
 and you will become my witnesses in Jerusalem, Judea, Samaria,

785
00:38:35,040 --> 00:38:36,160
 and to the ends of the world."

786
00:38:36,960 --> 00:38:41,040
 In other words, I'm not moving on the church so that you'll become a bless me club.

787
00:38:41,040 --> 00:38:44,000
 I'm not moving on the church so you're like something up on a hill

788
00:38:44,000 --> 00:38:45,120
 and everything like that.

789
00:38:45,120 --> 00:38:48,160
 I'm moving on the church so that the church can move on the world.

790
00:38:48,160 --> 00:38:51,600
 Think about it this way.

791
00:38:51,600 --> 00:38:53,520
 I think what church does when people come to Christ,

792
00:38:53,520 --> 00:38:55,840
 it's like it empties the world, that's awesome.

793
00:38:55,840 --> 00:38:58,160
 But then the church should empty itself back into the world.

794
00:38:58,160 --> 00:39:01,040
 There's this flow of happening.

795
00:39:01,040 --> 00:39:05,440
 And so bearing witness is the idea of us being that public faith

796
00:39:05,440 --> 00:39:08,960
 we spoke about last year, of having the joy in us,

797
00:39:08,960 --> 00:39:13,360
 to be people of Jesus proudly in the places that he's planted us in,

798
00:39:13,360 --> 00:39:15,200
 sharing the gospel.

799
00:39:15,200 --> 00:39:16,960
 And so what we want to do over the coming years

800
00:39:16,960 --> 00:39:20,080
 is to help all of us be better equipped to share the gospel,

801
00:39:20,080 --> 00:39:23,040
 whether that's with our colleagues, with our family members.

802
00:39:23,040 --> 00:39:25,680
 Many of you in this room are first generation Christians,

803
00:39:25,680 --> 00:39:27,120
 only Christian in your family.

804
00:39:27,120 --> 00:39:31,120
 How do we help you to equip you to share your life and your testimony

805
00:39:31,200 --> 00:39:35,520
 and your love of Jesus effectively to the people around you?

806
00:39:35,520 --> 00:39:36,880
 We want to help you to do that

807
00:39:36,880 --> 00:39:39,200
 because we believe that God is calling us to grow the kingdom.

808
00:39:39,200 --> 00:39:42,720
 So it's about bringing the gospel to Hong Kong

809
00:39:42,720 --> 00:39:45,680
 in a window of grace that we currently have in our city.

810
00:39:45,680 --> 00:39:48,240
 But it's also not just about speaking the gospel,

811
00:39:48,240 --> 00:39:50,240
 it's about living the gospel.

812
00:39:50,240 --> 00:39:52,240
 It's about justice.

813
00:39:52,240 --> 00:39:54,880
 And this has been always one of the central focuses

814
00:39:54,880 --> 00:39:58,000
 and hearts of the Vine is this area of justice.

815
00:39:58,000 --> 00:40:00,960
 And in this bearing witness, it's not just about sharing the gospel,

816
00:40:00,960 --> 00:40:04,320
 it's also about living out the priorities of a heart of justice,

817
00:40:04,320 --> 00:40:07,360
 serving the poor and the vulnerable and the marginalized,

818
00:40:07,360 --> 00:40:09,440
 using our resources to do that,

819
00:40:09,440 --> 00:40:14,560
 spreading around Asia the idea of God's heart for justice.

820
00:40:14,560 --> 00:40:18,480
 It's one of the things that I'm convinced is lost in the church at this time.

821
00:40:18,480 --> 00:40:22,480
 What does it really mean for us to hold a heart of evangelism and justice

822
00:40:22,480 --> 00:40:24,320
 in the church in the season ahead?

823
00:40:24,320 --> 00:40:25,360
 That's bearing witness.

824
00:40:25,360 --> 00:40:27,040
 Here's the final one.

825
00:40:27,040 --> 00:40:30,400
 And this one is perhaps the one that I get really excited about.

826
00:40:30,960 --> 00:40:32,880
 This is the sale.

827
00:40:32,880 --> 00:40:35,520
 See the symbol there?

828
00:40:35,520 --> 00:40:36,960
 The sale of church planting.

829
00:40:36,960 --> 00:40:39,440
 Now, you know that we've been speaking to you guys

830
00:40:39,440 --> 00:40:42,240
 about church planting quite a lot over the last little season.

831
00:40:42,240 --> 00:40:44,800
 In fact, God has been speaking to us about this

832
00:40:44,800 --> 00:40:46,480
 for probably five plus years now.

833
00:40:46,480 --> 00:40:50,240
 But church planting and why it's a bowl and stuff,

834
00:40:50,240 --> 00:40:51,520
 we'll tell you about that in a few weeks time

835
00:40:51,520 --> 00:40:52,960
 when we talk more about this.

836
00:40:52,960 --> 00:40:55,840
 But church planting has been on our heart for some season.

837
00:40:55,840 --> 00:40:57,360
 God has always said this to us,

838
00:40:57,360 --> 00:41:00,080
 but just during my sabbatical in 2024,

839
00:41:00,080 --> 00:41:01,600
 God said something very clear to me.

840
00:41:01,600 --> 00:41:04,560
 He said, "Andrew, my excitement for the future of the vine

841
00:41:04,560 --> 00:41:07,680
 is not its seating capacity, but its sending capacity."

842
00:41:07,680 --> 00:41:13,520
 Not its seating capacity, but its sending capacity.

843
00:41:13,520 --> 00:41:16,480
 And so this drives what we're sensing the Lord wants us to do.

844
00:41:16,480 --> 00:41:20,160
 We want to grow God's kingdom in the church.

845
00:41:20,160 --> 00:41:22,160
 We don't want to just keep adding services.

846
00:41:22,160 --> 00:41:24,880
 We want to see people come to faith,

847
00:41:24,880 --> 00:41:28,480
 but we don't want to just try to keep people coming into one place.

848
00:41:28,480 --> 00:41:31,280
 When a church is planted in a specific community,

849
00:41:31,280 --> 00:41:34,000
 it can reach the needs of that community more than ever before.

850
00:41:34,000 --> 00:41:36,640
 And so over the years, we've done this.

851
00:41:36,640 --> 00:41:38,160
 So here's a map of Hong Kong.

852
00:41:38,160 --> 00:41:39,680
 I want you to have a look at this.

853
00:41:39,680 --> 00:41:42,800
 We've been here in Wan Chai since 2011.

854
00:41:42,800 --> 00:41:46,240
 We had our first services in here in 2011.

855
00:41:46,240 --> 00:41:49,120
 Prior to that, we founded as a church in '97

856
00:41:49,120 --> 00:41:50,720
 and we moved throughout Hong Kong,

857
00:41:50,720 --> 00:41:53,840
 but we came to this current home in 2011.

858
00:41:53,840 --> 00:41:57,360
 Now back in October of 2023,

859
00:41:57,360 --> 00:42:01,920
 right when everybody else was like kind of closing down shop because of COVID,

860
00:42:01,920 --> 00:42:03,520
 we planted a new church.

861
00:42:03,520 --> 00:42:05,760
 We sent out a bunch of us to Yuen Long.

862
00:42:05,760 --> 00:42:11,040
 We held our first services in our church in Yuen Long in October of 2023.

863
00:42:11,040 --> 00:42:13,840
 Pastor Tim, who's the lead pastor there,

864
00:42:13,840 --> 00:42:17,040
 Pastor Ivan, June, and Chapman, and the others that work with them

865
00:42:17,040 --> 00:42:18,640
 are doing an amazing job.

866
00:42:18,640 --> 00:42:22,400
 In 2023 October, we sent out 30 people from Wan Chai

867
00:42:22,400 --> 00:42:24,320
 to go and plant this church in Yuen Long.

868
00:42:24,320 --> 00:42:28,160
 They now, just three years later, have 350 people gathered

869
00:42:28,160 --> 00:42:31,120
 on a weekly basis there, which is amazing.

870
00:42:31,120 --> 00:42:36,880
 And a number of those are people that are new to Jesus,

871
00:42:36,880 --> 00:42:38,800
 people that are coming to faith

872
00:42:38,800 --> 00:42:41,120
 through the work that's planted there, and we love it.

873
00:42:41,120 --> 00:42:42,400
 Now towards the end of last year,

874
00:42:42,400 --> 00:42:45,440
 we told you the exciting news that we're about to plant again.

875
00:42:45,440 --> 00:42:46,560
 We said that God had called us

876
00:42:46,560 --> 00:42:49,520
 to the northern metropolis side of Hong Kong

877
00:42:49,520 --> 00:42:53,360
 and that Sidney and Vivian Yip were feeling the call as pastors here

878
00:42:53,360 --> 00:42:55,200
 to go and plant a church there.

879
00:42:55,200 --> 00:42:57,360
 And I'm excited to tell you today the actual location.

880
00:42:57,360 --> 00:42:59,520
 We're going to be planting in Sheung Shui.

881
00:42:59,520 --> 00:43:02,720
 So there's a church plant that is going to be happening in Sheung Shui,

882
00:43:02,720 --> 00:43:06,960
 which is really exciting for multiple reasons.

883
00:43:06,960 --> 00:43:09,440
 They have a booth downstairs.

884
00:43:09,440 --> 00:43:11,680
 So right after the service, if you want to connect with them

885
00:43:11,680 --> 00:43:14,800
 and chat with the people, they've got, funnily enough,

886
00:43:14,800 --> 00:43:18,560
 they've got 30 people right now that are excited about going with them

887
00:43:18,560 --> 00:43:20,240
 to plant a church in Sheung Shui.

888
00:43:20,240 --> 00:43:23,120
 And we're hoping to start services there in the next couple of months.

889
00:43:23,520 --> 00:43:26,960
 Now, what's really important to know about our church plant in Sheung Shui

890
00:43:26,960 --> 00:43:30,560
 is that it's different to what we're doing in Wan Chai and in Yuen Long.

891
00:43:30,560 --> 00:43:34,880
 They're not going to be a Sunday gathering centric church.

892
00:43:34,880 --> 00:43:38,320
 They're going to be a discipleship and community centered church.

893
00:43:38,320 --> 00:43:40,560
 What that means is, and I love this,

894
00:43:40,560 --> 00:43:42,960
 they're not going to find, at least currently,

895
00:43:42,960 --> 00:43:46,160
 not going to find a physical place to renovate and build

896
00:43:46,160 --> 00:43:47,600
 to have Sunday services.

897
00:43:47,600 --> 00:43:50,240
 Instead, what they've discerned as a team

898
00:43:50,240 --> 00:43:51,840
 is that God is asking them to rent.

899
00:43:51,840 --> 00:43:54,640
 This is quite radical, quite risky, quite exciting,

900
00:43:54,640 --> 00:43:58,800
 renting a shop front on one of the busiest streets in Sheung Shui,

901
00:43:58,800 --> 00:44:00,880
 right near the MTR, a shop front,

902
00:44:00,880 --> 00:44:03,200
 renovating about a thousand square feet there,

903
00:44:03,200 --> 00:44:06,560
 not to hold services, but actually to do community outreach

904
00:44:06,560 --> 00:44:08,320
 Monday to Friday from that place.

905
00:44:08,320 --> 00:44:11,920
 Now, what they're going to do then is they're going to partner

906
00:44:11,920 --> 00:44:15,760
 with a church in Sheung Shui who only have services in the morning,

907
00:44:15,760 --> 00:44:19,280
 and they're going to hold their service in the afternoon in that church

908
00:44:19,280 --> 00:44:22,160
 so that they don't have to buy, renovate, make whatever.

909
00:44:22,160 --> 00:44:25,280
 They're going to put their resources into the outreach

910
00:44:25,280 --> 00:44:26,560
 rather than into the gathering.

911
00:44:26,560 --> 00:44:27,600
 Does that make sense?

912
00:44:27,600 --> 00:44:28,720
 I love this vision.

913
00:44:28,720 --> 00:44:32,560
 And so they're going to, we've already worked to help to find,

914
00:44:32,560 --> 00:44:35,040
 and they're working hard to find a shop front.

915
00:44:35,040 --> 00:44:37,120
 And so when we sent Yun Long out,

916
00:44:37,120 --> 00:44:39,120
 we said that we were going to support them.

917
00:44:39,120 --> 00:44:41,360
 We're going to do the same with Sheung Shui.

918
00:44:41,360 --> 00:44:42,720
 And let me tell you about that in a second.

919
00:44:42,720 --> 00:44:44,000
 So these are the four cells.

920
00:44:44,000 --> 00:44:44,720
 Does that sound good?

921
00:44:44,720 --> 00:44:46,720
 Does that excite you to a degree?

922
00:44:47,760 --> 00:44:51,760
 Part of vision is to resource, and God always resources the vision.

923
00:44:51,760 --> 00:44:53,840
 So let me just very quickly, as we draw to a close,

924
00:44:53,840 --> 00:44:56,240
 tell you about the resourcing we need.

925
00:44:56,240 --> 00:44:58,160
 Now, I want to be honest with you to say this.

926
00:44:58,160 --> 00:44:59,520
 We don't know everything that we need.

927
00:44:59,520 --> 00:45:03,200
 There may be stuff happening around the corner that we're not aware of.

928
00:45:03,200 --> 00:45:06,160
 So we don't know everything that we need right now,

929
00:45:06,160 --> 00:45:10,080
 but we do have an idea of some of the critical pieces for this step

930
00:45:10,080 --> 00:45:12,000
 where we do need to raise some money.

931
00:45:12,000 --> 00:45:13,440
 And that's what we're going to be inviting all of you

932
00:45:13,440 --> 00:45:16,560
 across our services today to stand together as one church

933
00:45:16,560 --> 00:45:18,560
 in raising resource towards this.

934
00:45:18,560 --> 00:45:22,400
 First of all, on this side, we're wanting to raise about $1.5 million

935
00:45:22,400 --> 00:45:25,840
 for this side, if you will, of the sales.

936
00:45:25,840 --> 00:45:29,120
 One of the things that we recognize here in our building in Wan Chai

937
00:45:29,120 --> 00:45:32,560
 is that oftentimes the building works against us

938
00:45:32,560 --> 00:45:36,720
 when it comes to wanting to deepen community and growth and discipleship.

939
00:45:36,720 --> 00:45:39,920
 You'll know this very well, particularly if you're here at the 11 o'clock most weeks.

940
00:45:39,920 --> 00:45:44,480
 It's like we get like, you know, 800 of us flowing into the room

941
00:45:44,480 --> 00:45:45,920
 and then flowing out of the room.

942
00:45:45,920 --> 00:45:48,080
 And it feels like there's no place to linger.

943
00:45:48,080 --> 00:45:49,760
 There's no place to slow down.

944
00:45:49,760 --> 00:45:52,640
 There's no place to actually get to know each other, get connected.

945
00:45:52,640 --> 00:45:56,320
 And as well as changing the structure of our services to help with that,

946
00:45:56,320 --> 00:46:00,320
 we also want to change some of the structure of our building to help with that.

947
00:46:00,320 --> 00:46:04,560
 So we're looking to raise $1.5 million today to help renovate

948
00:46:04,560 --> 00:46:09,520
 some of the spaces here in Wan Chai so that you will have a better place to go,

949
00:46:09,520 --> 00:46:12,320
 to connect, to build community, to be discipled.

950
00:46:12,320 --> 00:46:13,360
 We've got some ideas.

951
00:46:13,360 --> 00:46:15,280
 You're going to hear about them in the weeks ahead,

952
00:46:15,280 --> 00:46:20,160
 but we're hoping to raise about $1.5 million to renovate some of our space for that.

953
00:46:20,160 --> 00:46:24,400
 On this side of the equation, first of all, with the idea of bearing witness,

954
00:46:24,400 --> 00:46:29,680
 we're looking to raise $1 million today in this area for development of our justice work

955
00:46:29,680 --> 00:46:31,840
 that we do as a church, $1 million.

956
00:46:31,840 --> 00:46:36,160
 Most of that will probably go to the development of our conference.

957
00:46:36,160 --> 00:46:39,520
 If you've been here at the Vine, you'll know that we've run a justice conference.

958
00:46:39,520 --> 00:46:43,280
 We had run it for about nine years prior to 2019.

959
00:46:43,280 --> 00:46:47,840
 And then from 2019 to 2025, it was shut down because of all the things that were happening.

960
00:46:47,840 --> 00:46:50,240
 We started it again last September.

961
00:46:50,240 --> 00:46:51,600
 It was a great success.

962
00:46:51,600 --> 00:46:55,360
 And we want to get some seed funding to be able to continue to grow that conference,

963
00:46:55,360 --> 00:46:57,440
 not just in Hong Kong, but around Asia.

964
00:46:57,440 --> 00:47:02,480
 And with that, we believe that the Lord is asking the Vine to be a place where we can

965
00:47:02,480 --> 00:47:08,640
 gather people and teach them about a heart for justice, gather practitioners and leaders from

966
00:47:08,640 --> 00:47:13,040
 around the world into these conferences in Asia to really deepen our understanding of

967
00:47:13,040 --> 00:47:14,400
 God's heart for justice.

968
00:47:14,400 --> 00:47:17,760
 It costs us about 500,000 Hong Kong to run a conference.

969
00:47:17,760 --> 00:47:21,120
 So over the next five years, we're hoping to do it every other year.

